text: Walked past this interesting small coffee place. The taste is rather nice. Feels slightly sweeter than most other coffee but nice and refreshing. The large cup is bigger than most other cafes which for me is good.
Ordered the mint latte and itâ€™s nice. Nothing exceptional though. Environment is comfortable during off peak. I hope they survive the competition located alongside big players like % and Equate.
Coffee blend has fairly nice aroma, pleasant, well-rounded.  Tried the watermelon latte, which is ok, refreshing for a hot day. However, doesn't pack a wow factor.

The black sesame gelato is really mid... the insides were really melted and mushy and it had a minty flavour?? Is black sesame supposed to taste like mint?? My throat feels lowkey uncomfortable...Maybe get their coffee or sth but don't try the gelato ðŸ¤¡
